Preheat your oven to 220°C/200°C fan/gas mark 7.

Trim and halve the @Chantenay Carrots{150%g} lengthways (no need to peel) and pop
them onto one half of a #baking tray{}. Drizzle with @oil{drizzle}, season with
@salt{} and @pepper{}, then set aside.

Halve, peel and thinly slice the @onion{1}(peeled and thinly sliced). Heat a
drizzle of @oil{drizzle} in a #frying pan{} on medium-high heat.

Once hot, add the onion and season with @salt{}, @pepper{} and the @sugar{1/2%tsp}.
Fry until soft and sweet, ~{8-10%minutes}.

While the onion cooks, wrap a rasher of @British Streaky Bacon{6} around each
@British Honey Mustard Sausages{6} in a spiral so they're fully covered. Pop the
bacon wrapped sausages onto the other half of the carrot baking tray.

When the oven is hot, roast on the middle shelf until the sausages are golden
brown and cooked through and the carrots are tender, ~{20-25%minutes}. Turn
halfway through.

> IMPORTANT: Wash your hands and equipment after handling raw meat. The sausages
> are cooked when no longer pink in the middle.

Meanwhile, bring a large #saucepan{} of water with @salt{1/2%tsp} to the boil
for the potatoes.

Trim and thinly slice the @spring onion{1}(trimmed and thinly sliced). Peel and
chop the @potatoes{450%g}(peeled and chopped into 2cm chunks).

When the pan of water is boiling, add the potatoes and cook until you can
easily slip a knife through, ~{15-20%minutes}.

Once the onion is soft and caramelised, add the @water{400%ml for the jus} to
the #pan{}.

Bring to the boil on high heat, then stir in the @Red Wine Jus Paste{44%g} and
reduce the heat to medium. Allow the sauce to bubble and thicken, stirring
regularly, ~{7-8%minutes}.

Once glossy and thickened, pour into a #bowl{} or #gravy jug{} and cover to
keep warm.

Meanwhile, once the potatoes are cooked, drain in a #colander{} and return to
the pan, off the heat. Add the @creme fraiche{75%ml} and mash with a
#potato masher{} until smooth.

Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}, then stir in the spring onion and
@wholegrain mustard{17%g}. Taste and add more seasoning if needed. Cover with a
#lid{} to keep warm.

Just before you are ready to serve, wipe out the frying pan and pop it back on
medium-high heat with a drizzle of @oil{drizzle}.

Once hot, add the @peas{120%g} and stir-fry for ~{2-3%minutes}.

When everything is ready, share the mash between your plates and top with the
bacon wrapped sausages.

Serve the peas and carrots on the side. Reheat the onion jus (if needed) and
pour over to finish. Enjoy!